					<h4><a href="http://www.linux.com/feature/141548">In memoriam: Linux evangelist and Linux.com editor Joe Barr</a></h4>
				<blockquote><p>Our colleague Joe Barr sometimes described himself as a doddering old geek. Many knew him as a Linux evangelist; others knew him from his ham radio activities. And those of us who worked with Joe knew him in all of his sometimes irascible, often funny moods. Joe was always one of our favorite people, and we are devastated to report that he died at home, unexpectedly, last night.</p>

<p>His wife Susan asks that instead of sending flowers, you make a donation to an animal rescue group of your choice in Joe's name.</p></blockquote>

<p>Rest in piece Joe. You will be sorely missed :-(</p>

<p>From: <a href="http://www.linux.com/feature/141548">Linux.com</a>.</p>
