					<h4><a href="http://www.jejik.com/articles/2008/03/helios_solutions_added_to_our_portfolio/">HeliOS Solutions added to our portfolio</a></h4>
				<p>A little over a month ago I linked to <a href="http://www.jejik.com/articles/2008/01/linux_for_the_masses_bet_on_this_winner/">an interview with Ken Starks</a> a.k.a. Helios about his new company HeliOS Solutions. HeliOS Solutions is a small not-for-profit Linux company in the United States of America. All of their profits go to the Komputers4Kids program, which recycles old computers, installs Linux on them and gives them away to children who need them for school work.</p>

